b'[![](../../cdshop/cdinfo.jpg)](../../cdshop/index.htm)  \n[Sacred Texts](../../index.htm)  [Hinduism](../index.htm)  [Index](index.htm)\n[Previous](av045.htm)  [Next](av047.htm)\n\n* * *\n\n## VI, 136. Charm with the plant nitatni to promote the growth of hair.\n\n1\\. As a goddess upon the goddess earth thou wast born, O plant! We dig thee\nup, O nitatni, that thou mayest strengthen (the growth) of the hair.  \n2\\. Strengthen the old (hair), beget the new! That which has come forth render\nmore luxurious!  \n3\\. That hair of thine which does drop off, and that which is broken root and\nall, upon it do I sprinkle here the all-healing herb.\n\n* * *\n\n[Next: VI, 137. Charm to promote the growth of hair](av047.htm)\n\n'